In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on March 1, 2017, he acknowledges the significant contributions made by Irish Americans to the United States. He highlights the millions of Americans of Irish descent who enrich various aspects of American life and mentions notable figures such as the Founding Fathers and Thomas Francis Meagher. Trump emphasizes the hard work, resilience, and entrepreneurial spirit of Irish immigrants throughout history. He also recognizes the cultural influence of Irish Americans in literature, cinema, music, dance, sports, and visual arts. Trump calls for the celebration of Irish-American Heritage Month in March, urging Americans to honor the achievements and contributions of Irish Americans through appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.